Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.51,0:00:21.04,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Never ignore the power of deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.28,0:00:22.78,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Its limits rely on the wielder!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.84,0:00:24.48,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The game is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.68,0:00:26.21,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's time for another case's reasoning show!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.81,0:00:28.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Recognizing that single truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.28,0:00:30.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.22,0:00:32.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.56,0:01:45.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}At the game center, we were taking pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.93,0:01:48.50,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Until we noticed someone playing a shooting game...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:52.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Teitan High School English teacher, Jodie Saintemillion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.87,0:01:57.91,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She showed Ran a game to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.77,0:02:02.21,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She was quickly beat by Bitou Kengo{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.88,0:02:11.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That is until we discovered Bitou{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} had been murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.65,0:02:13.82,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We gathered the suspects...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.96,0:02:17.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A writer named Shimizu Takayasu{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.39,0:02:20.96,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An employee of the game center, Dejima Hitoshi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.86,0:02:24.50,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A taxi driver, Emori Toshitsugu{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:26.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.23,0:02:28.07,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Jodie{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-sensei{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.37,0:02:34.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who is the one that committed the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.81,0:02:41.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's something about that match,\NI know there's something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.82,0:02:45.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Also, what about the weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.89,0:02:48.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We didn't find it on anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.52,0:02:52.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be that the killer still has it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.73,0:02:55.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.56,0:02:58.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Where is the culprit's weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.09,0:03:07.77,Title,Sign,0,0,0,,The Battle Game Trap\N(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.57,0:03:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Battle Game Trap, Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.61,0:03:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was picking up a 100 yen coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.78,0:03:15.65,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Emori Toshitsugu (41)\NTaxi Driver
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.15,0:03:16.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I was buying some coffee from the\Nmachine but dropped my change.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.38,0:03:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I admit I didn't like the guy, but I respected him as a gamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous, didn't he taunt\Nyour skills at a driving game?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.70,0:03:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.47,0:03:36.27,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Shimizu Takayasu (30)\NGame Journalist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.60,0:03:38.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he told the other visitors: "If you wanna\Nlive, stay out of this guy's taxi."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.94,0:03:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you not have a better motive for killing him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.64,0:03:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that guy was your sister's boyfriend, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.98,0:03:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His sister's boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.02,0:03:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His sister, Imoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and that guy were living together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.96,0:04:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since he was your gaming partner, you\Ncouldn't say anything to him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you, young man, you wanted him dead as well, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.83,0:04:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.74,0:04:14.58,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Dejima Hitoshi (22)\NStore Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.34,0:04:15.78,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Half-a-year ago, this young man was\Nknown as the best gamer in Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.41,0:04:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he disappeared after losing a big match to the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.61,0:04:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess he decided to change his hairstyle and work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.19,0:04:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, we have found traces\Nof poison in the victims blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.36,0:04:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.63,0:04:36.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The poison found was tetrodotoxin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.86,0:04:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it entered through the right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.70,0:04:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Tetrodotoxin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.07,0:04:44.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Fugu!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.44,0:04:48.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tetrodotoxin, TTX for short.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.64,0:04:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even just half of a miligram to one miligram can prove fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.72,0:05:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If ingested, the fugu fish's poison works its way through the bloodstream slowly, giving the victim a chance to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.03,0:05:10.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's directly injected, it means instant death. The End.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.33,0:05:19.97,Character Card,Sign,0,0,0,,Teitan High School Teacher\NJodie Saintemillion (28)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.73,0:05:19.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Or at least that's what a doctor friend of mine told\Nme, he said you have to be careful of it in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.91,0:05:24.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As I thought, that's why the weapon was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.48,0:05:28.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go back and look for clues at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.75,0:05:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is everyone fine with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.05,0:05:33.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.29,0:05:40.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it, that's the sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.06,0:05:42.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But from where?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.33,0:05:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, your left shoelace is untied.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, thanks, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should always keep it tied, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.84,0:05:58.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.61,0:06:01.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That person killed Bitou{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.52,0:06:06.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And used the game center's environment to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.89,0:06:12.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But why did that person do it in front of the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.53,0:06:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? Can we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, we searched the entire place\Nand found nothing like a needle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The security cameras tell us that no one left during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.56,0:06:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the culprit may still have the weapon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.87,0:06:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.57,0:06:59.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, we need everyone to submit themselves to a search.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.41,0:07:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can if you want, it makes no difference to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.41,0:07:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy died fighting me, I didn't even have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.52,0:07:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't either, I was only near Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nbefore the match to collect the coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.16,0:07:30.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one you should be looking for a weapon on is\NEmori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was near him during the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.70,0:07:35.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what about the woman playing\Nthe racing game beside Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.48,0:07:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, didn't we tell you? Jodie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}\Nplayed that game the entire time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.98,0:07:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.99,0:07:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, it can't be done from this game chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.46,0:07:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While sitting at this race game, you\Ncan't reach over there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.06,0:07:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that she wasn't involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.07,0:08:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I should remind you all that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.04,0:08:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was injected from the right side, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.18,0:08:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was on the left so it couldn't have been me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.11,0:08:18.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now now everyone, we're just investigating every angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.12,0:08:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.29,0:08:29.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, I'm rather disappointed. Especially\Nwith you, Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.06,0:08:35.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal is smirking right in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.60,0:08:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.34,0:08:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was injected from the right side,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.77,0:08:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means Emori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} couldn't have been responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.75,0:08:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} talked with him before the battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.75,0:08:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't kill him because Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nspoke with the victim just afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.66,0:09:04.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since we were watching Jodie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} play\Nthe racing game, it couldn't have been her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.33,0:09:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the only one remaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.10,0:09:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the only one remaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.14,0:09:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one that hated the victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.55,0:09:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the only one remaining...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.78,0:09:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one that hated the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimizu Takayasu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:33.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.56,0:09:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.20,0:09:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't everyone see me lose the battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.34,0:09:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I have killed him despite that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.41,0:09:54.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't try that on me, I already knew you would say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.85,0:09:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.72,0:09:58.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, Officer Takagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sit where they were playing the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.96,0:10:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This will help make everything clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.13,0:10:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please sit here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.13,0:10:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.37,0:10:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? The police are taking orders from a young girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.71,0:10:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.21,0:10:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It started?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.08,0:10:31.52,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.49,0:10:39.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that guy being rough with that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.73,0:10:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't he an officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.80,0:10:45.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.20,0:10:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.91,0:10:57.18,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}K.O.!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.95,0:11:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was merciless...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.98,0:11:02.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.82,0:11:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, I know you're competitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.46,0:11:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you were playing too hard that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.79,0:11:15.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} told Officer Takagi\Nto use the female character.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And told him to cover his eyes with his necktie\Nso he could do nothing during the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.60,0:11:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the one using the male character...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.34,0:11:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko told me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.41,0:11:31.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.15,0:11:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A mind trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.22,0:11:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, it's a natural impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone expected Ran to be the female\Nand Officer Takagi as the male, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.19,0:11:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in fact, it's just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.23,0:11:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} chose Beika Caesar,\Nand that Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} chose Haido Lucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.17,0:11:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is exactly how we were fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.71,0:12:05.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this game doesn't display a hit-point gauge,\Nit's hard to tell who is playing as which character.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.85,0:12:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if the players' characters are\Nswitched, no one would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.12,0:12:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you mean Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s was changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.99,0:12:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, after being attacked by Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand his needle, he either died or fainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.33,0:12:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tetrodotoxin is known to cause instant paralysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.50,0:12:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he didn't faint, he wouldn't\Neven have been able to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.64,0:12:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait, if he were poisoned before the\Nfight, wouldn't the crowd have noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.15,0:12:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.12,0:12:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was playing the game, I didn't actually use\Nany strength and let the machine move my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.23,0:13:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The game chair's chest guard kept my body in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.04,0:13:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made this his trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.14,0:13:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before the battle, you went over to Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand pricked him under his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.91,0:13:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was feeling the\Neffects, the game was started...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.05,0:13:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A battle where the victim would be Lucas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.32,0:13:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After doing this, you ran over to your game and picked\NBitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s character Beika Caesar before pressing OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.13,0:13:38.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, the crowd would think that you\Nwere the one being beat by the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.51,0:13:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why didn't he deliver the final blow on the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.91,0:13:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he would have ended the match that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.11,0:13:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s game screen would say "You Lose."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With a tie, it would say "Draw."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.46,0:14:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that it would only say "Game Over."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.76,0:14:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.00,0:14:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't a needle still have to be around here, girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.30,0:14:12.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't remember them finding such a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.04,0:14:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I wanted to search you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.61,0:14:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and search me, you won't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.82,0:14:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's actually right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.35,0:14:29.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he doesn't have the weapon with him any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.72,0:14:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.49,0:14:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weapon is walking all around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.50,0:14:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.03,0:14:40.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.97,0:14:42.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.67,0:14:46.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.24,0:14:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.88,0:14:52.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.18,0:14:54.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.32,0:14:57.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, you didn't notice, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.02,0:15:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sound of metal scratching the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.26,0:15:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.73,0:15:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be, your shoe has...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.19,0:15:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.13,0:15:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Placed the needle in a cigarette, kept it there with\Ngum, and made it stick to the gum wrapper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.94,0:15:20.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.71,0:15:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could just place it on the floor and\Nit wouldn't matter who stepped on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.62,0:15:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did this by saying it was to pick up his lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.62,0:15:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since it was in the cigarette,\Nall he had to do was flatten it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.89,0:15:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The carrier wouldn't notice it if it were flattened, and\Neven if they did, they would just throw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.17,0:15:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, whether or not you removed the poison is questionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.31,0:16:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you set the tobacco up beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likely in the game center's restroom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.25,0:16:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you set it up in the cigarette box,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.29,0:16:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be as suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.96,0:16:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, if we can find Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints\Non the cigarette, we should have our evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.93,0:16:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your reasoning has impressed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.07,0:16:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this was all set up, girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.84,0:16:32.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That tobacco and gum are different than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.75,0:16:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.81,0:16:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, someone must be setting me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.35,0:16:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone knows I chew gum for\Nluck, it was even in a magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.79,0:16:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can test for my fingerprints,\Nbut you won't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.90,0:16:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! It's like that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.10,0:17:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't figure out why you used the gum to discard the\Nweapon, even after chewing gum in front of the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.94,0:17:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, I discovered that you likely just took the gum\Nand cigarette from an ash tray in the game center.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.22,0:17:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only reason you chewed gum was\Nin case they found the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.82,0:17:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This would be a way to prevent\Nthe police from suspecting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.26,0:17:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wouldn't he leave fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.97,0:17:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he wouldn't leave any if he held\Neverything between his fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.98,0:17:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, to remove the wrapped needle, all\Nhe had to do was squeeze the packaging.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.12,0:17:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about the coin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.39,0:17:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, would you please open\Nthe coin box on that machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.66,0:17:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.10,0:18:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be three 100-yen coins inside now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.67,0:18:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recall you removing the coins from\NBitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s machine earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.74,0:18:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please check the amount of coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.71,0:18:13.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.72,0:18:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.48,0:18:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be one coin from Bitou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.56,0:18:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And another from when Officer Takagi played.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.96,0:18:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's another, used during the\Nkiller's trick to have an extra game.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.07,0:18:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I know that that third\N100-yen coin has your fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.61,0:18:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how will we know before testing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.15,0:18:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be, as Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't\Nknow the coins were collected.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.35,0:19:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since he didn't have a chance to wear gloves,\Nhis fingerprints must be on that coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.56,0:19:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without gloves, he couldn't have covered his fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.94,0:19:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My fingerprints are there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.31,0:19:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I tightly gripped that 100-yen coin...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.01,0:19:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As that was my "Last Game."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.25,0:19:20.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Last Game?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.31,0:19:26.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was saying goodbye to games and that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.52,0:19:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's for my sister, who's going blind...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.06,0:19:33.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's going blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.36,0:19:36.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know why she's going blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.76,0:19:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's due to a lack of vitamin A.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.27,0:19:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.07,0:19:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To pay off that guy's huge amount of gambling debts,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.81,0:19:54.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She worked for an entire month and hardly ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.85,0:19:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after that guy joined a gang, she still didn't leave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you wanted to play the victim in one last game?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.62,0:20:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy said if I beat him at that game,\Nhe would leave my sister alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.37,0:20:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I tried my best to beat him as Haido Lucas...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.34,0:20:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I just couldn't beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.58,0:20:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that's why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.31,0:20:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but now I regret doing it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.92,0:20:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because now that the Beika Caesar is gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.42,0:20:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll never have a chance to beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.45,0:22:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! That was impressive, Sonoko. Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.52,0:22:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were really cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.72,0:22:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were like Kate Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.69,0:22:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.36,0:22:19.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, that American, female police officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.46,0:22:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But really, you were deducing like Shinichi back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.23,0:22:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.00,0:22:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Wasn't he the one that appeared at the festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.10,0:22:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He is so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.21,0:22:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not that good, he's just a reasoning otaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.84,0:22:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye Sensei, we have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.01,0:22:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Jodie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.92,0:22:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye bye, I'll see you at school tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.19,0:22:57.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bye bye, Cool Guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.27,0:23:10.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right, much happened today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.88,0:23:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to admit, this place isn't so boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.12,0:23:20.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already located one of the targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.35,0:23:24.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's changed his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.29,0:23:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.50,0:23:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The target's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.36,0:23:32.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.77,0:23:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Rotten Apple."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.30,0:23:39.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's use that codename, alright?
